ch: occupational name for a buyer or merchant, Middle Dutch <i>coper</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Kuiper","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Dutch Gerrit, Hendrik, Willem, Harm, Klaas, Kort, Marinus, Nicolaas, Wouter.","Dutch: occupational name for a cooper, Middle Dutch <i>cup(e)re</i>."]},{"name":"Couper","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Cooper  ."]},{"name":"Hooper","meanings":["English (southwestern): occupational name for a cooper, someone who fitted wooden or metal hoops on wooden casks and barrels, or a barrel-maker, from Middle English <i>hoper</i>, an agent derivative of <i>hop</i> ‘hoop, band’. Compare   Cooper  ."]},{"name":"Coop","meanings":["English (Lancashire): metonymic occupational name for a cooper, from Middle English <i>coupe</i>, <i>cupe</i> ‘tub, cask’ (from Latin <i>cūpa</i>), probably used for a cooper; compare   Cooper  . In some cases the surname may have been derived from a pub or house sign.","Americanized form of German or Dutch   Koop  .","History: It was David Koop (his father's surname also spelled <i>Kupe</i>) from Germany whose surname was changed to <i>Coop</i> after he settled in PA toward the end of the 18th century. He later moved to VA."]}]},{"name":"Symon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."],"variants":[{"name":"Simen","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Symon Cooper was born in 1290, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Sir Symon Cooper Earl of Fife."},"et":{"1290–":"1290–Surnud","1290–1350":"1290–1350","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1320":"1320","1350":"1350","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1290–":"1290–Kuollut","1290–1350":"1290–1350","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1290–Female":"1290–Kuollut","1320":"1320","1350":"1350","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1290–":"1290–Décédée","1290–1350":"1290–1350","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1290–Female":"1290–Décédée","1320":"1320","1350":"1350","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Écosse","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs Symon Cooper est née en 1290, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir Symon Cooper Earl of Fife."},"de":{"1290–":"1290–Verstorben","1290–1350":"1290–1350","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1290–Female":"1290–Verstorben","1320":"1320","1350":"1350","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mrs Symon Cooper wurde 1290 in England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit Sir Symon Cooper Earl of Fife mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1290–":"1290–Desede","1290–1350":"1290–1350","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1290–Female":"1290–Desede","1320":"1320","1350":"1350","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland","England, United Kingdom":"Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"1290–":"1290–elhunyt","1290–1350":"1290–1350","1320–1380":"1320–1380","1290–Female":"1290–elhunyt","1320":"1320","1350":"1350","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland","England, United Kingdom":"Anglia, United Kingdom"},"id":{"1290–":"1290–Telah Meninggal","1290–